      <References/>
      <Content>It may be of interest to note that in Greek NT manuscripts καθάπερ and καθώσπερ are often alternative forms. As in the case of ὥσπερ and ὡσπερεί ({D:64.13}) in contrast with ὡς[a] and ὡσεί[a] ({D:64.12}), so καθάπερ and καθώσπερ appear to be somewhat more emphatic than καθά and καθώς[c] ({D:64.14}).</Content>
